&lt;ul style=&quot;margin-top: 0cm;&quot;&gt;
 &lt;/ul&gt;The proposed first floor side and rear&amp;nbsp;extension, by reason of its siting and excessive width and depth, would result in a loss of outlook, light and overshadowing and overbearing impact to the first floor rear windows at No. 71 Gainsborough Gardens and an overbearing impact to the side/rear amenity space of No. 75 Gainsborough Gardens,&amp;nbsp;to the detriment of the&amp;nbsp;residential amenities of the neighbouring occupiers,&amp;nbsp;contrary to the National Planning Policy Framework (2023), Policy D3, D.7 of the London Plan (2021), Policy DM 1 of the Harrow Development Management Policies Local Plan (2013) and the adopted Supplementary Planning Document: Residential Design Guide (2010).&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul style=&quot;margin-top: 0cm;&quot;&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ol style=&quot;margin-top:0cm&quot; start=&quot;1&quot; type=&quot;1&quot;&gt;
 &lt;/ol&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:12pt&quot;&gt;The proposed first floor side and rear extension in conjunction with the existing single storey rear&amp;nbsp;extensions on the host property, by reason of excessive and incongruous cumulative bulk and massing, as well as poor and awkward design, on a prominent&amp;nbsp;plot, would result in an incongruous, contrived and unduly obtrusive form of development, to the detriment of the character and appearance of the existing property and wider street scene, contrary to the high quality design aspirations of the National Planning Policy Framework (2023), Policy D3 (D(1) and D(11)) of The London Plan (2021), policy CS1 B of the Harrow Core Strategy (2012),&amp;nbsp;Policy DM1 of the Harrow Development Management Policies Local Plan (2013) and the adopted Supplementary Planning Document: Residential Design Guide (2010).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;ol style=&quot;margin-top:0cm&quot; start=&quot;1&quot; type=&quot;1&quot;&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
